<p class="subtitle_page_programme margin_bottom_20">Cancellation and Refund Policies</p>
<p class="margin_bottom_20"><strong>Cancellation by applicant:</strong></p>
<ul class="lista_con_pallini margin_bottom_20">
<li>Summer School registrations will not be confirmed until registration is complete and billing information is received in full</li>
<li>Cancellations received <strong>before 20 June 2021</strong> will be fully reimbursed minus <strong>50,00 €</strong> of administrative fees</li>
<li>Cancellations received <strong>after 20 June 2021</strong> will be charged <strong>50% of the total fee</strong>. Alternatively, the enrolment can be transferred to another Venice based programme or to the 2022 edition of CHRA (fees may have to be compensated if not similar)</li>
<!--<li>Cancellations <strong>after 30 April 2020</strong> will be charged <strong>100%</strong> of the total fee.</li>--></ul>
<p class="margin_bottom_20"><strong>Cancellation by Global Campus of Human Rights:</strong></p>
<ul class="lista_con_pallini margin_bottom_20">
<li>The Global Campus of Human Rights is not responsible for any extra expenses (i.e. travel costs, Visa, etc.) incurred by the participant if a programme is cancelled.</li>
<li>If the course is cancelled due to any unforeseen circumstances such as weather or natural disaster, the participant is entitled to reschedule for a future session.</li>
<li>The Global Campus of Human Rights reserves the right to cancel any programme due to insufficient number of applications up to the deadline for enrolment. Notice will be provided with the full refund of registration fees minus 50,00 € of administrative fees.</li>
</ul>